triggering a brand new electrical wave in the next cell.

507
00:23:54.600 --> 00:23:57.280
And through the magic of neuroplasticity,

508
00:23:57.280 --> 00:23:59.800
every single time you fire that sequence,

509
00:23:59.800 --> 00:24:02.160
the physical structure of your brain becomes

510
00:24:02.160 --> 00:24:04.680
a little bit stronger, a little bit more efficient.

511
00:24:04.680 --> 00:24:07.760
Which leads us with a final, slightly provocative thought

512
00:24:07.760 --> 00:24:10.320
to ponder as you review your notes.

513
00:24:10.320 --> 00:24:11.240
Oh, lay it on us.

514
00:24:11.240 --> 00:24:12.940
If every single thought you think,

515
00:24:12.940 --> 00:24:16.280
every behavior you repeat, and every new skill you practice

516
00:24:16.280 --> 00:24:19.840
physically alters the microscopic strength, structure,

517
00:24:19.880 --> 00:24:22.840
and chemical balance of your synaptic connections.

518
00:24:22.840 --> 00:24:25.400
Then from a purely neurobiological standpoint,

519
00:24:25.400 --> 00:24:27.400
the brain you woke up with this morning

520
00:24:27.400 --> 00:24:30.400
is physically, structurally different from the brain

521
00:24:30.400 --> 00:24:31.840
you will go to sleep with tonight.

522
00:24:31.840 --> 00:24:35.320
You are, quite literally, constantly rewiring

523
00:24:35.320 --> 00:24:37.040
the physical nature of your own identity.

524
00:24:37.040 --> 00:24:38.760
What a thought to end on.

525
00:24:38.760 --> 00:24:40.680
Keep exploring those simulations.

526
00:24:40.680 --> 00:24:43.400
Pay attention to the tension in the resting state.

527
00:24:43.400 --> 00:24:45.600
Watch how the chemicals bridge the gap.

528
00:24:45.600 --> 00:24:48.400
And thank you for joining us on this deep dive.
